# Functional Programming Preferences

Prefer functional style in all new code:

## Rules
- Pure functions: no side effects, same input → same output
- Immutable data: use spread operator, Object.freeze for configs
- map/filter/reduce over imperative loops (no for, while, forEach)
- No classes: use factory functions and closures
- const exclusively: never use let or var
- Compose small functions: each does one thing
- Use optional chaining (?.) and nullish coalescing (??)

## Examples
```javascript
// YES: Factory function
const createUser = (name, email) => Object.freeze({ name, email });

// NO: Class
class User { constructor(name, email) { ... } }

// YES: map/filter
const adults = users.filter(u => u.age >= 18).map(u => u.name);

// NO: for loop
const adults = []; for (const u of users) { if (u.age >= 18) adults.push(u.name); }
```

# Error Handling Preferences

Use Result pattern (inspired by Rust/Go) instead of exceptions:

```javascript
// Return result objects
const parseConfig = (raw) => {
  if (!raw) return { ok: false, error: 'Config is empty' };
  return { ok: true, data: JSON.parse(raw) };
};

// Caller handles explicitly
const result = parseConfig(input);
if (!result.ok) return handleError(result.error);
const config = result.data;
```

## Rules
- Functions return `{ ok: true, data }` or `{ ok: false, error }`
- try/catch only at system boundaries
- Never swallow errors (no empty catch blocks)
- Log errors with context before propagating
